com.yahoo.bullet.record.avro

Class LazyBulletAvro

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yahoo.bullet.record.avro.LazyBulletAvro
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<Map.Entry<String,Serializable>>

    public class LazyBulletAvro
extends Object
implements Serializable, Iterable<Map.Entry<String,Serializable>>
    This class wraps all Bullet compatible AVRO data and makes it lazily de-serializable. The data is reified only when needed to. It operates on AVRO SpecificRecord types. Subclasses should override serialize(Map) and reify(byte[]) to go back and forth between the AVRO serialized data and a Map of fields. You can also just override write(Map, Encoder) and read(Decoder) if you wish to use the existing reading and writing process used in serialize(Map) and reify(byte[]).
